node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jim Gaffigan in Radio City Music Hall with @jimjefferies. May be an image of text that says 'Hollwood SUBSCRIBE It's unclear why the show is changing locations, but the Winter Garden Theatre has significantly less seating capacity than Radio City Music Hall or the Beacon Theatre, which also has hosted the Tonys in recent years. Nothing appears to be scheduled at Radio City for the night of Sept. 26 per the venue's website, though Jim Gaffigan is booked for four nights immediately prior to the Tony Awards date, which presumably wouldn't give enough time to set up and rehearse for the Tonys. The Beacon Theatre also is booked a couple nights prior with Jim Jefferies shows.'.

node.text: I love how comedians who had to reschedule shows (3x) due to the pandemic are presented as somehow bumping the @thetonyawards out of Radio City and The Beacon in the @hollywoodreporter.  I rescheduled my September 22-25 dates a year ago.  I literally only need @radiocitymusichall for like 4 hours a night. How much rehearsal in a venue do you need? I know @thehughjackman & @suttonlenore could make it work.  They are so talented and they both strongly encourage you to buy tickets to any of my FUN TOUR shows at jimgaffigan.com.
